'''Biophotovoltaic''' is an adjective used to define a device in which a fraction of the electrons produced during the [[oxidation]] of water by [[photosynthesis]] are transferred onto an [[anode]] and then to a [[cathode]] where an electrically driven process takes place.<ref>http://www.cheng.cam.ac.uk/research/groups/electrochem/research/BPV.html</ref>

For information about the technology, see [[biological photovoltaics]].
