{{Infobox power station | name = East Bend Generating Station | image = Rising-sun-indiana-ohio-river--from-above.jpg | image_caption = East Bend Generating Station from a distance. The plant is located behind [[Rising Sun, Indiana]] in this view from the north. | location_map = USA Kentucky | country = United States | location = [[Boone County, Kentucky|Boone County]], near [[Union, Kentucky]] and [[Rising Sun, Indiana]] | coordinates = {{coord|38.90|N|84.85|W|region:US-KY_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | owner = [[Duke Energy]] | status = | th_fuel_primary = [[Bituminous coal]] | th_cooling_source = [[Ohio River]] | th_combined_cycle = | ps_units_operational = 1 | ps_electrical_capacity = 669 [[Megawatt|MW]] | commissioned = 1981 | decommissioned = }}
The '''East Bend Generating Station''' is a [[coal-fired power plant]] owned and operated by [[Duke Energy]] near [[Rabbit Hash, Kentucky]]. It is located 10 miles west of [[Florence, Kentucky]]. The closest city is [[Rising Sun, Indiana]], which lies to the northwest, across the [[Ohio River]]. Originally planned for four units, only unit no. 2 was built and is in commission.
