{{expand Russian|topic=transport|otherarticle=Катастрофа Boeing 727 под Тегераном|date=January 2017}}{{Infobox Aircraft accident |name=Iran Air Flight 291<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=JPNdAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Zl8NAAAAIBAJ&pg=4961,3030975&dq=iran+air+flight+291&hl=en Iran Air Boeing crashes]</ref> |Date= {{start-date|January 21, 1980 }} |Type=Inoperable ILS and ground radar |image=Boeing 727-86, Iran Air AN2176292.jpg |caption=An Iran Air Boeing 727-100, similar to the one involved. |occurrence_type=Accident |Site=[[Alborz Mountains]], Iran |Fatalities=128 |Survivors=0 |Aircraft Type=[[Boeing 727|Boeing 727-86]] |Origin=[[Mashhad Airport]] (MHD/OIMM), Iran |Destination=[[Mehrabad Airport|Tehran-Mehrabad Airport]] (THR/OIII), Iran |Operator=[[Iran Air]] |Tail Number=[http://www.airliners.net/search/photo.search?regsearch=EP-IRD&distinct_entry=true EP-IRD] |Passengers=120 |Crew=8 }} '''Iran Air Flight 291''' was a flight that crashed on January 21, 1980. The flight, carried on a [[Boeing 727|Boeing 727-86]], was making a domestic flight from [[Mashhad International Airport|Mashad Airport]] to [[Mehrabad Airport|Tehran-Mehrabad Airport]] in Iran. At 1911h local time, the aircraft, registered as EP-IRD, collided with the [[Alborz Mountains]], {{convert|29|km}} north of [[Tehran]], during its approach to Tehran-Mehrabad runway 29 in foggy and snowy weather conditions.<ref name=asn>{{ASN accident|id=19800121-0}}</ref> All 8 crew members and 120 passengers died in the incident, and the plane was destroyed.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=x9JWAAAAIBAJ&sjid=c0INAAAAIBAJ&pg=6244,740316&dq=iran+air+crash&hl=en 128 feared dead in Iran Air Crash]</ref> At the time, Iran Air Flight 291 was the deadliest aircraft disaster in Iranian history.
Investigators concluded that the probable cause of the crash was believed to be an inoperable [[instrument landing system]] and ground [[radar]].<ref name=asn/> The head of Iran's Civil Aviation Authority and five other officials were charged with manslaughter<ref>{{cite book |title=Aviation Disasters Second Edition |last1=Gero |first1=David |publisher=Patrick Stephens Limited |year= 1996 |page=161 }}</ref> as a result of the crash of Flight 291.
