The '''Lakdhanavi Power Station''' (also sometimes referred to as the '''Lakdhanavi Sapugaskanda Power Station''') is a {{Nowrap|24 [[Megawatt|MW]]}} thermal power station built in [[Sapugaskanda]], [[Sri Lanka]]. Operated by {{Nowrap|Lakdhanavi (Private) Limited}}, it is one of three power stations in the Sapugaskanda region, the other two being the government-owned {{Nowrap|160 MW}} [[Sapugaskanda Power Station]], and the {{Nowrap|51 MW}} [[Asia Power Sapugaskanda Power Station]].<ref name=TheIsland2001>{{cite news|last1=Perera|first1=Ranjith|title=Power crisis and shortsighted policies|url=http://www.island.lk/2001/07/05/featur02.html|accessdate=8 November 2015|publisher=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]]|date=5 July 2001}}</ref> {{Clear}}
